1.title: Landscape Challenges
1.plot: Every home improvement project brings it's own unique challenges. These yards have problems include a dangerous kids' play set, a crumbling deck and a yard devoid of living plants.

2.title: Beast to Beauty
2.plot: Antonio and his team bring beauty and livability to these homeliest of homes. These are the biggest transformations he's done so far.

3.title: Patching Up a Break-In
3.plot: Tyra is a vibrant mom with a close-knit family. Unfortunately their house was broken into and their belongings were stolen. Now Antonio and his team will bring some happiness with a completely remodeled kitchen.

4.title: Lemonade Stand to Fight Cancer
4.plot: Antonio wants to give back to a charitable family. Drew and Toney have a loving family that has been through hard times. Their family bond has remained strong as they've both battled cancer, and Toney is a decorated veteran.

5.title: A Whole Lot of Mulch
5.plot: Jennifer is been is so busy with work and taking care of her family that her huge yard has grown out of control. Can Antonio and his team of landscapers and gardeners, and a big pile of mulch tame this wild yard?

6.title: Honeymoon House
6.plot: Terri and Kyle are an adorable recently engaged couple. They just moved in together but haven't had a chance to fix their living room. Hopefully Antonio and his team can help them build the house where they can start their family.

7.title: Pretty Pictures
7.plot: Banner is a professional photographer that needs to renovate her photography office/studio. She would normally do the repairs herself, but unfortunately health problems have derailed her project.

8.title: Radical Renovations
8.plot: Antonio loves to help families in need. These deserving families will get brand new radical renovations that are completely unexpected and bring these families joy.

9.title: Horseshoe Pit Party
9.plot: Tony and Jennifer have had a hard year with Jennifer's father passing away and their oldest son away in the Marine Corps. With all of this turmoil their backyard has fallen into disrepair. Now Antonio can bring happiness to this family.

10.title: The Long Room
10.plot: Hannah and Bobby recently pooled their resources to buy a house. Unfortunately all they could afford was a fixer-upper with an unwieldy long room. They need designer Ryland Woodard's help to make this odd-shaped room functional.

11.title: Fresh Flowers from Stephen
11.plot: Eva is the single mother of Stephen who has cerebral palsy. Now that Stephen is no longer a toddler, Eva needs a new patio so Stephen can play outside and enjoy his flowers. Antonio and the community pitch in to build them a terrific deck.

12.title: Bocce Backyard
12.plot: April is a young, successful woman who doesn't have time to renovate the empty space in her backyard. She wants to be able to entertain friends, and what better way to do that than with a brand new bocce ball court and patio?

13.title: Bedroom Masters
13.plot: Antonio and his crew give tips and advice how to renovate Master Bedrooms and how to make the most important rooms into the houses more luxurious and give a feeling of comfort and relaxation.

14.title: Sisters Need Space
14.plot: The Walker sisters have shared a cramped bedroom for a year and nerves are starting to get frayed. Can Antonio and his team restore this bedroom to bring relaxation to these deserving siblings?

15.title: Wrecking Rooms
15.plot: Antonio is really good at demolitions. These are the most difficult demolition problems he's faced, and the amazing transformations afterwards.

16.title: Family Game Night
16.plot: Banner and her two boys want to turn their shed into a game room. But the room isn't safe and after they discover an animal infestation in the insulation, their problems get worse. Hopefully Antonio and his team can come to their rescue.

17.title: Mud Hole Makeover
17.plot: Gerald and his mom have a dismal, empty backyard that's practically a mud hole. They need Antonio and his team to work some serious magic on this sad yard, to bring life and color to this deserving family.

18.title: Sad Stories, Happy Endings
18.plot: Antonio and his crew help families down on their luck by transforming their rooms into amazing new spaces. Tears are shed, but now these families can start their lives in their wonderful new homes.

19.title: Zingy Zinc Table
19.plot: Antonio and his team are faced with a desolate backyard that needs some help. They bring in a brand new patio and a custom-made zinc table for this family that loves to grill together.

20.title: Unique Spaces
20.plot: Antonio and his team sometimes are called in for unusual renovations. These are some of his biggest projects including renovating the roof of the Old Capitol Inn and the Louis Armstrong Foundation in New Orleans that was damaged in Katrina.

21.title: Luscious Living Room
21.plot: Betty's living room is dysfunctional. Her living room is outdated and boring. Can Antonio and his team bring form and function to this malnourished living room and turn it luscious and colorful?

22.title: Indecision Bedroom
22.plot: Antonio and his team help renovate a master bedroom for an indecisive family that can't find the time to finish their home. They've had paint swatches on the walls for eight months. Now they will finally have their home fixed and finished.

23.title: Boyhood Bedroom
23.plot: Michael is an enthusiastic young man who has grown up in this bedroom, but now that he's 21 he really needs an updated, organized room fit for an adult.

24.title: Fish Tank Office
24.plot: Antonio and his team have to deal with a massive fish tank in the middle of an otherwise empty office. Can they take an empty room and turn it into a bright and productive office space?

25.title: Miracle Modernized Kitchen
25.plot: Rene and John Anderson are so excited when Antonio and his team arrive. Their kitchen is plain and devoid of personality. Antonio and crew will update and renovate the kitchen to bring the cabinet into the 21st century.

26.title: Garage Boutique
26.plot: Jeanette's garage has become a storage room for her grandchildren's belongings. She wants them to be able to play in there so Antonio will transform this dirty, old storage area into a playroom.

27.title: A Unique Attic
27.plot: Ramsey is a contractor who has been promising his teenage daughter a new bedroom for ten years. Now Antonio and his team will bring a unique approach to decorating the attic with a pulley-opening door and hanging furniture.

28.title: Where's Our Grass?
28.plot: Nicole is a working mom who needs a new yard. There is no grass in the yard and the soil is just not very good. So Antonio and his team will bring some synthetic grass and stylish furniture to make this backyard bloom again.

29.title: The Professor's Master Bedroom
29.plot: Michael is a professor who is so excited when Antonio knocks on his door. That means he's finally getting a bedroom renovation. Michael's house was apparently built "before they invented closets."

30.title: Better Living
30.plot: Antonio and his crew visit Montgomery, Alabama, Louisville, Kentucky and Jackson, Mississippi in this compilation of greatest living room renovations.

31.title: Not Just for Parking
31.plot: Antonio and his crew visit Louisville, Kentucky and Tucson, Arizona in this compilation of greatest garage renovations.

32.title: Backyard Beauties
32.plot: Antonio and his crew visit Jackson, Mississippi and Memphis, Tennessee in this compilation of greatest pergola designs.

33.title: Basement Hangouts
33.plot: Antonio and his team give advice how to transform dirty, dingy basements into fun, livable family rooms.

34.title: Nicki's Creation
34.plot: Designer Nicki Huggins brings her stylish pizzazz to three houses that really need her Hollywood sparkle. These are the most remarkable transformations she's made.

35.title: More Than Meets the Eye
35.plot: Antonio and his crew take three run-down rooms and transform them into completely new spaces. The outcomes are completely unexpected.

36.title: What's Cooking?
36.plot: Antonio and his crew give tips and advice how to renovate kitchens and we tackle some of the toughest kitchen transformations yet.

37.title: Outdoor Adventures
37.plot: Antonio and his team of landscapers bring tips and advice how to renovate backyards and turn them from muddy pits into beautiful fully functioning yards.

38.title: Weathering the Storm
38.plot: Antonio and his crew have faced all kinds of weather, but these are some of the harshest storms yet, from torrential downpours to three feet of snow in Cleveland, Antonio always delivers.

39.title: Magical Transformations
39.plot: Antonio and his crew bring their "A" games to some of the biggest home transformations yet. These are the biggest, most breath-taking renovations we've seen.

40.title: Home Office Extravaganza
40.plot: Antonio and his crew give tips and advice how renovate home offices, making them more functional and showing how to maximize space in these neglected rooms.

41.title: The Kids Are All Right
41.plot: Helping kids is one of Antonio's favorite parts of his job. These are some of the most memorable kid-friendly transformations. Antonio brings joy to these children by bringing in child-safe, parent approved fun rooms.

42.title: Poolside Paradise
42.plot: Not everyone is lucky enough to have a pool. And not everyone who has a pool is lucky enough to have a great backyard. But after Antonio gets done with these swimming pools you will get some ideas how to make your backyards sparkle.

43.title: Helping Out Single Moms
43.plot: Antonio loves to help families, especially kids. These are hard-working mothers that need a little help finishing their homes, and if that's all they need to be happy Antonio and his Team are up for the task.

44.title: Amazing Outdoor Spaces
44.plot: Curb appeal is one of the most important things for a happy home. Antonio and his team of yard specialists will make these homes beautiful and inviting.

45.title: Porches & Patios
45.plot: Porches and patios are some of the most challenging rooms. They are small, and neglected. But Antonio and his team will give tips and advice how to bring out the personality of these sad, little spaces.

46.title: Happy Kids Rooms
46.plot: Antonio loves helping out kids. His team of designers will give advice and tips on how to bring a personal touch to make these rooms appealing to children.

47.title: Repurposed Rooms
47.plot: Some of Antonio's hardest projects are fixing up rooms and repurposing them as something completely new. Projects include turning an office into a girl's bedroom and an old attic into a family room.

48.title: Jungles to Jewels
48.plot: If a yard is left untended too long it turns into a jungle. This is where Antonio and his team come in. They will tame back these wild landscapes and turn them into backyard jewels.

49.title: Unique Decorators
49.plot: We feature some of the best decorators from the Fix It and Finish It team.

50.title: Fun & Games
50.plot: Antonio loves to help families and have a good time while doing it. These are three fun and games projects that you can build in your own backyard including a bocce ball court and a horseshoe pitch.

51.title: Worthy Causes
51.plot: Antonio loves to help families in need. These are three of the most deserving families who have faced unbelievable obstacles. When you can do a small favor for someone that transforms their life you know Antonio will do it.

52.title: Fighting the Good Fight
52.plot: Antonio and his team love to support our men and women in the U.S. Armed Forces. These are three worthy families who work in various branches of the military who all badly need a home renovation.

1.title: Proper Parlor Party
1.plot: Mardi Gras will be running through the space that Antonio makes over in this NOLA party house. With the help of his team, Courtney Bullock receives a makeover she can only dream of.

2.title: Backyard Blues
2.plot: Fernando and Alexis Cortez are surprised when Antonio's crew show up with dump trucks, excavators and any heavy duty equipment you can imagine, to give them a new backyard.

3.title: Poolside Oasis
3.plot: Antonio surprises Irene and her parents with a brand new shaded zen den. In hopes to have a space for her mother to enjoy, the Fix It team makes her dreams a reality.

4.title: Baby Makes Three
4.plot: In Tucson, Arizona, Antonio surprises Brian and Stephanie John. With their first baby on the way, the team overhauls what he calls a man cave, into a family cave.

5.title: A Diamond in the Porch
5.plot: The Barron's playroom and connecting porch are in need of Antonio's help. Unpleasing to the eyes and full of mismatching furniture, this upstairs living area stands out from the rest of the put together home.

6.title: Mid-Century Mudpit
6.plot: In Birmingham, AL, Antonio surprises Wes Charles and Dana Fleming in the early morning. They are overly thrilled and give Antonio a tour of the area in their home they need the most help in, their backyard's non-existing patio that's currently a mud pit.

7.title: Happy House
7.plot: As a single mother, Phyllis would love a space where her family can hang out and bring friends over; a space to come together and relax. Antonio surprises the Phyllis and her two girls, to give them a "Happy Home" they will love.

8.title: Master Bedroom Madness
8.plot: Antonio and his team want to give Megan and Craig a retreat they deserve. This master bedroom will feel like vacation everyday for these busy parents.

9.title: Wedding Wasteland
9.plot: Brooke and Carl, a relaxed couple live with their seven-year daughter, Sophia. In hopes' to have a wedding in the backyard, they desperately need Antonio's help.

10.title: Driveway Demolition
10.plot: Victoria and Morris were pleasantly shocked by Antonio's early morning surprise visit, especially when revealed to them that they will be receiving a front yard makeover.

11.title: A Lofty Bedroom
11.plot: Antonio surprises the Erickson's, who want to give their son Isaac a new bedroom. The team promises Isaac a new room that he will be proud to show to his friends.

12.title: Landscape Loss
12.plot: Antonio and his team ambush a family with some serious back yard problems. With a landscape facelift, a happy couple's dreams come true.

13.title: Updated Heirloom
13.plot: Carol loves her home; it originally belonged to her father and after he passed, has become hers. Antonio makes over this living room that's not lived in.

14.title: Eclectic Excitement
14.plot: The Fix It team meets Sam and Chris Daughtry. They have a new baby and an old house. Giving them a fresh new living room to match their eclectic style, Antonio does 2 rooms at once!

15.title: Curb Appeal
15.plot: Tyler Coats wants to bring a life to this neighborhood and make his porch a Cajun celebration! Antonio and his team help revive this area in transition.

16.title: Money Pit
16.plot: Antonio and the team turn this tool-shed back into the master bedroom that Chad and Rachel deserve.

17.title: Bare Basement
17.plot: Antonio and his crew surprised the Morse family with a new family room. They now have a functional space for their family to grow and have friends over.

18.title: Hideaway Haven
18.plot: Bren Broussard wants to have a backyard haven for her mother to enjoy. This overgrown pool area is going to become a perfect slice of New Orleans after Antonio and team arrives!

19.title: Organized Mess
19.plot: The Fix It Team surprise a mother daughter duo, who need help keeping their work organized. Antonio's team transforms a storage space into a work area.

20.title: Duplex Demolition
20.plot: In this episode, Antonio decides to pay a visit to the loving family, The Johnson's! Antonio and his crew have a plan to turn this "Storage room" into a functional, comfortable and homey living room.

21.title: Palm Springs Paradise
21.plot: Antonio and his Fix it & Finish It team have come up with a design to not only revitalize Jonathan's neglected backyard, but to help improve his cooking space and party atmosphere.

22.title: Deck Disaster
22.plot: Soon to be parents, Rachel and Scott call Antonio to the rescue! Because of the layout of their existing and hazardous deck, their side yard is inaccessible, so they rarely spend time in it.

23.title: Side Room Shananigans
23.plot: Antonio surprises Eric and Melanie, a happily married pastor and teacher with an office project on their hands. Eric & Melanie are thrilled and overjoyed to have Antonio at their door.

24.title: Basement Buddies
24.plot: Eric Carwell and his son, Eric, are energetic and funny men, with a strong father-son bond. With Eric not having the funds or time to renovate their basement, it would be nice to have Fix It & Finish It's help, as the room is currently used as a dumping ground.

25.title: Tropical Oasis
25.plot: Lori Tantawai, is married to Abraham, a US Army Captain who is currently serving the country in Afghanistan. With Abraham away, Lori has taken charge of fixing the yard. and turns to Antonio for a Caribbean retreat!

26.title: Bricks, Bricks, and More Bricks
26.plot: Rebecca and Jodi bought a home together but unexpected sewer and roof repairs have exhausted their savings. Can Antonio and his team bring some plants and color to this couple's lifeless yard?

27.title: Outdoor Organizing
27.plot: With a busy schedule, Pierre and Krista are in need of a getaway space. The garage is unorganized and they want to have a retreat from their 5 kids. Antonio can't wait to surprise the family, and that, he does.

28.title: Man Cave Makeover
28.plot: The Davis family man cave has turned into a storage closet. Antonio and his team create a new space for their whole family to enjoy. The new space is so to be the best hangout in the neighborhood.

29.title: Pirates of the Pool
29.plot: The Dudenhefer's need Antonio to help bring life and color to their gray concrete pool patio, and to help build their son's pirate ship playground.

30.title: Living Legend
30.plot: Eddie "Duke" Edwards is a living legend in New Orleans. Antonio and his team will bring back jazz to this home that has been quiet for years.

31.title: Barren Backyard
31.plot: Antonio surprises Nicole and gets a walk through of her fun home, but bare backyard. She's a first time homeowner, tired of working on the inside of the home, and ready for a relaxing outdoors oasis.

32.title: Termite Turmoil
32.plot: Antonio meets Elaina, a sweet, single mother of two. Their current storage room would be a perfect master bedroom for her, away from the kids' rooms, but it's overflowing of books, bikes, and loads of miscellaneous items.

33.title: Reverse Ambush
33.plot: Privilege, a single mother of two from Zimbabwe, moved to New Orleans to start a new life for her two daughters. Antonio was touched by Privilege's story and is extremely motivated for this fix.

34.title: Stay-cation
34.plot: Antonio's team takes on project sun room. The McIntosh family wants a place where they can have as a stay-cation.

35.title: Couture Kitchen
35.plot: Melanie feels embarrassed to entertain with her kitchen in the shape that it is, but nonetheless she pleads and begs for Antonio to come and fix and finish it.

36.title: The Giving Yard
36.plot: In Birmingham AL, Kristina pleads for Antonio to come to her house and give her the relaxing backyard that she has always wanted, instead of something that she refers to as "Another task on my to do list.

37.title: Shiny New Sunroom
37.plot: With full time jobs, working almost six days a week, Eric and Mallory believe Antonio's help would be a life changing experience. They would like to use their sun room to entertain, but firstly, remove the painted AstroTurf.

38.title: Jungle Gym
38.plot: In Jackson, Mississippi, the Fix it and Finish It team help the Edwards transform a backyard into a playground.

39.title: Shipwreck of a Bedroom
39.plot: Antonio and his team meet the Lewis's', a deserving family with 6 boys and not enough beds.

40.title: Light at the End of the Hall
40.plot: Antonio and his team help a single Mother Tiffany and her Son Miles. Changing the room from dark to light would give the Wheeler's a fresh new outlook into their future.

41.title: New Lease
41.plot: Jean Sabastian and LaShonda Rene have weathered many trials over the years. The Fix It and Finish Team surprise them with a new living room.

42.title: Deck Down Below
42.plot: After hiring a bad contractor, Rick and Dana were left with a hazardous deck and no repair in sight. Antonio and the Team Houseworks come to the rescue.

43.title: Healing Wounds
43.plot: Pam Pybas and Miriam Sacibal are a couple living in Ridgeland, Mississippi. Their kitchen has many issues that need to be resolved. In it's dilapidated state, it is a reminder of a hard time in the couple's life.

44.title: Bocce Buddies
44.plot: Single Dad, Marcus Burger wants to have a safe backyard for his two children. Antonio makes his dreams come true.

45.title: Double the Fun
45.plot: Jenell and Brena are both twin sisters and first time homeowners. Currently their backyard is barren. The only structural features are fire ant hills, and old fence and a drainage swell.

46.title: Cats in the Kitchen
46.plot: Darren and Malia live in their house in Jackson, Mississippi with their one year-old Evan, but their cats get more use out of their kitchen than they do. Antonio will help them completely remodel and update their old-fashioned kitchen.

47.title: Old Capital Inn
47.plot: Antonio is brought in to refurbish the roof area of the family-owned Old Capitol Inn in downtown Jackson, turning it into a stylish lounge.

48.title: Bricks in the Wall
48.plot: Rachel and Christopher spend their free time doing charity work and have never had the time to finish their empty office. Antonio helps them tear down the wall to their backyard.

49.title: Shed to a Sunroom
49.plot: Antonio helps clear out a room filled with storage, and gives a mother and daughter the sun-room they've been dreaming about.

50.title: Helping Out a Friend
50.plot: When tragedy strikes the Shelley family Antonio brings together a team of local contractors to help finish an uncompleted deck project.

51.title: Jungle in the Backyard
51.plot: Daniel and Anna Beth are a young couple with a backyard that's overgrown and out of control. It will take Antonio and a huge landscaping team to trim a massive tree and build a beautiful arbor in the untamed jungle of a yard.

52.title: You Work in a Closet
52.plot: Catherine and Alan Smith have a tiny home office. They need Antonio to help turn this cramped closet into a functional office with desk, living area and extra storage. Is Antonio up to the large task in a small space?

53.title: Family Room Disaster
53.plot: Dave and Claire live with their two sons live in a beautiful home in Memphis, Tennessee. Dave has been using the family room as a workroom while refurbishing their home.

54.title: Music to My Ears
54.plot: We meet Reginal and his beautiful family. They are in need of a serious renovation of their home recording studio. He would also love this studio to be renovated to be able to work from home a lot more to spend time with his family.

55.title: Living Room Gymnasium
55.plot: The Curry family's living room is currently a storage space for exercise equipment. But Fredrika would love to have a comfortable living area to spend more time with her three girls.

56.title: My Dad Fell Through the Ceiling
56.plot: Brad and his father Steve have been renovating their family home together. Can Antonio and his team bring some love to this family and update and finish their kitchen in under 12 hours?

57.title: Lightning in Mama's Kitchen
57.plot: The Diffee family have a cramped old-fashioned kitchen that was actually struck by lightning. Is this a sign that Antonio will help them remodel their kitchen?

58.title: Shotgun Shack Wedding
58.plot: Robin and Patrick are getting married and want to convert their storage room into an extra bedroom. Antonio and his team bring secret tips on how to maximize the space of a small room.

59.title: Purple Porch and a Pink Door
59.plot: First time homeowner Samantha has a sad front porch. She would love something vibrant with pretty colors and some landscaping. Antonio and his team have some offbeat ideas, like a purple porch and a pink door.

60.title: Grandma's Porch Swing
60.plot: Newlyweds Patrick and Rachel refurbished the interior of their home themselves. But they ran out of money when it came time to finish their front porch.

61.title: Fine Dining in the Garage
61.plot: Maggie and Kline are expecting their second child. Their home is too crowded for another kid so they want to convert their garage into a dining room.

62.title: Bringing Light to the Living Room
62.plot: Antonio and his crew help a family that's been dealing with tragedy. Their oldest son was hit by a car, and plans on refurbishing their home has been put off, until now.

63.title: Modern Family Room
63.plot: Mike and Ryan are college sweethearts that are looking to get married and have a child but their house is too small. Although they're ready to adopt a more adult lifestyle their living room is stuck in their college days.

64.title: Industrial Style in the Backyard
64.plot: Antonio and his crew are heading to the first home of Mason Meredith and Becca Burrus. They have spent a lot of money renovating the house but they are now out of time, money and energy and need help with their incomplete deck.

65.title: Backyard Mud Pit
65.plot: Derek and Kay are newlyweds who just purchased their first home, a 1904 Victorian shotgun. Their backyard is a muddy mess and it will take Antonio to work his magic to give them the best backyard possible.

66.title: 1970's Kitchen Nightmare
66.plot: Jesse and Megan are a young and recently engaged couple. They are first time homeowners with a 1975 kitchen nightmare. Now it's up to Antonio and his team to give them a stylish and modernized kitchen.

67.title: In Need of a Clean, New Kitchen
67.plot: Brad and Ashlie live in their old home with their three kids. One of their daughters Hallie is fighting leukemia. Since Hadley can't be around dust or construction, Antonio's mission is to refurbish and sanitize their kitchen.

68.title: Loft Playroom
68.plot: Frank and Liz kids don't want to bring their friends over to spend time in their old-fashioned, cluttered loft playroom. Antonio and his team will bring pizzazz to this boring room and turn it into the coolest hangout ever.

69.title: A Backyard for the Troops
69.plot: Ben and Jami are both veterans and work for veteran services. They need Antonio and his team to transform their overgrown backyard into an outdoor sanctuary.

70.title: Living Room by the Lake
70.plot: Melissa and Steven have inherited their new home from Melissa's parents. Now Antonio and his team will rip down the peeling yellow wallpaper and make it into a beautiful lakeside retreat.

71.title: Bedroom for a Cleveland Cop
71.plot: Mark and his wife Ann have a dreary Master Bedroom that needs help. Antonio and his team will do a stylish bedroom renovation for this hard-working cop/fireman and will also throw in a bathroom makeover just for fun.

72.title: Pet Lovers Home Office
72.plot: Carlos and Michelle are trying to start a new online pet company. But their home office is tiny and cluttered with mementos from their old, failed business.

73.title: Flooded Family Room
73.plot: Pete and Therese recently experienced a flooded basement that wiped out their family room. But before Antonio and his team can implement their stylish new makeover they discover cracks in the foundation of the home.

74.title: Helpers to Homeless Need a Kitchen
74.plot: Tim and Amber work for the city of Cleveland trying to help the homeless problem after the economic downturn. But they need Antonio's help to rejuvenate their outdated, run-down kitchen.

75.title: Snowstorm Makeover
75.plot: Antonio and his team arrive during a Cleveland snowstorm. But like the Postal Service, two feet of snow and biting cold won't stop Antonio from delivering a stylish new kitchen to this young couple.

76.title: Backyard Patio and Dog Wash
76.plot: Antonio and his crew are going to refurbish the backyard for Brandon and April and their two young boys, and dogs. This couple lives by the river so they need some sort of dog washing/kid washing station.

77.title: New Attic for Newlyweds
77.plot: Chris and Bonnie are recent newlyweds. They tried to renovate their attic and turn it into an entertainment room. They didn't get very far so Antonio and his team have a lot of work turning this barren attic into a livable functioning room.

78.title: New Door to Happiness
78.plot: Antonio and his team help a family who struggled to keep their house through storm damage. A tornado blew their door off its hinges. Antonio wants to give them a fun updated family room where they can spend time together as a happy family.

79.title: Birds Nest in the Chimney
79.plot: Taylor and James are nice couple expecting a new baby, but their living room is sad and dreary. They need a bright, new living room and a working fireplace so that they can entertain when guests want to visit the new baby.

80.title: Front Porch Fiasco
80.plot: Sarah and Ricky have a closed in porch that needs help. The family can't afford to fix it up and the flooring, screens and lighting are all worn out. Now Antonio hammers to fix up and polish this space so the whole family can enjoy it.

81.title: Drab Office to Fabulous Bedroom
81.plot: Kirk and Lisa have an 11-year-old daughter Taylor who needs a bigger bedroom. They want to convert Kirk's drab old home office into a fabulous bedroom fit for a budding young entertainer.

82.title: Our Home Is Our Office
82.plot: Can Antonio help a couple whose office paperwork and files have taken over their entire house? Antonio and his team have their work cut out for them taming this office into a manageable space.

83.title: Baby's New Garden
83.plot: EunSung and Jocelyne have a newborn baby. Their backyard is barren which is sad because they both enjoy gardening. Antonio arrives to discover that their patio is rotting away and could've fallen down at any moment.

84.title: Pathetic Deck
84.plot: Jared and his Aunt have a pathetic deck and a yard that needs help. They love to garden, but are not very good at. Antonio and his team bring a dramatic new look to this deck.

85.title: Accidental Flooding
85.plot: Antonio and his team visit Josh and Jared to help organize their basement and find a place for all of their stuff they are storing there. But a seemingly simple job gets complicated when an accidental flooding stops the rebuild.

86.title: Dream Bedroom
86.plot: When Chris's Marine base closed he had to move his growing family as quickly as possible. Antonio and his team will help them move into their new home and give them their dream bedroom.

87.title: New Recruits
87.plot: Shawn and Angie are Army recruiters who have a new home. Their living room has been wrecked by their messy but adorable twins.

88.title: Garage Gym
88.plot: Casey and Marissa are fitness enthusiasts that just moved in together. All of her boxes took over the garage gym so that they can't work out. Antonio with Carolina Panthers Safety Roman Harper refurbish the gym of this deserving family.

89.title: Backyard Karoake Party
89.plot: Julie and Robert love to play with their kids in their backyard but they haven't been able to maintain the landscaping. Can Antonio and his team bring the fun and music back to their yard?

90.title: More Storage Please
90.plot: Jill and Jones and their children need a new family room. Their growing family is taking over the room and their carpet is impossible to keep clean.

91.title: National Guard Front Yard
91.plot: James is in the National Guard and donates his free time to help veterans with PTSD. Can Antonio and his team help this deserving veteran and make his front yard pretty and inviting?

92.title: Where's the Door?
92.plot: Cat and James donate their time to different charities and so they don't have the time or resources to renovate their family room. They want to be able to host parties for their kids, but they don't have a door to their master bedroom.

93.title: Comic Book Kitchen
93.plot: Rich is a police officer who writes comic books as a hobby. Rich has an outdated kitchen that really needs a face lift, but finances are tight. Now is time for Antonio to be the super-hero and renovate this kitchen in one day.

94.title: Sun Room with a View
94.plot: Rob and Cindy are a nice couple with a large family. But unfortunately their sun room is a neglected room being taken over by their pets. Antonio and his team are installing a heating unit that will make this an indoor/outdoor space.

95.title: Seeing the Light
95.plot: Antonio and his team are on a special project to help Michael and Robyn. Michael is suffering from Usher's syndrome, a rare disease that takes away his hearing and sight. He desperately needs help with his living room.

96.title: Painting the Grass Green
96.plot: Beth and Hunter just bought their house but didn't realize their huge backyard was going to be such a challenge to keep up. They have bills and no free time, so hopefully Antonio and his team can work their magic.

97.title: Allergic to My Own Yard
97.plot: Hunter just bought his new house and has discovered he's allergic to the bushes in his own yard. Hopefully Antonio and his team can swoop in and landscape this yard, bringing in plants and flowers that hopefully won't make Hunter sick.

98.title: Winning a Trophy Room
98.plot: Charlie and Kristi are competitive athletes. But since they've bought their home their bonus room as slowly acquired so many boxes that it's become a storage room.

imdb.title: Fix It & Finish It
plot: Fix It and Finish It is in a different city every day helping families in need with their homes, cabins and RV's needing a makeover inside and out. Host Antonio Sabato Jr and his team of designers remake a complete room in just one day.
